  "text": "Analogue data were acquired (before ca. 1994) at the RSP through principal short-period channels [CITATION_1] . One was a traditional low-gain (≈10 000) short-period system. The other two used a band-rejection filter peaked at 0.33 Hz to eliminate microseismic noise from sea swell: the high-gain short-period channel offered routine amplifications of ≈100 000 at 1 Hz, and the so-called T-wave channel used further high-pass filters to boost magnification in the seismoacoustic band (2-10 Hz) to as much as 2 × 10 6 at 3 Hz [CITATION_2] .",
